chaddr (1.0.1) testing; urgency=medium

  * CLI: rename --refetch to --renew; pass addr-history and spare sets through
    CLI renew like the GUI
  * Profiles: add profile_lexer with context-sensitive NAME ':' ARG* parsing
    (default bash-like shell words with quotes and escapes; COMMA_LIST for ns,
    host/hosts, and record/name attributes)
  * Profiles: addr-history parsed as whitespace-separated addresses (not commas)
  * Resource type: rename bind db to zone file (bind db remains a legacy alias)
  * AWS Elastic IP renew: list all EIPs in the region and release every address
    matching the current candidate set instead of failing when DescribeAddresses
    returns NotFound for a NAT/public IP
  * Aliyun Elastic IP renew: convert VPC NAT public IPs with
    ConvertNatPublicIpToEip before release; list/unassociate/release candidate
    EIPs; wait for Available status; surface Aliyun Code/Message on API errors
  * Zone file and hosts file apply/renew: match and replace all spare/old IP
    candidates (addr-history, resolve, --old-ip), not only the primary address
  * Handlers: profile-scoped spare snapshot for Apply preview separate from
    diagnose accumulation; orchestrator sets source addresses during renew
  * GUI: spare for diagnose/renew/apply comes from each profile file only, not
    from multi-selection or the Current addresses panel; multi-select runs
    concurrent independent operations
  * GUI: nested notebook placeholder pages to avoid GTK empty-tab assertions;
    BitmapButton and minimum-size flags for toolbar buttons on GTK
  * GUI: fix AddressEditFrame methods accidentally nested after a module helper;
    per-profile log/diagnostic tabs; reduce wxStyledTextCtrl focus churn
  * GUI: zone file diagnose labels and Apply preview with > prefix lines
  * address.py: spare_sets_from_entries ignores non-spare entries
  * Documentation and packaging: update README, man pages, bash completion,
    profile/example, and .gitignore for chaddr build artifacts

