chaddr (1.0.0) testing; urgency=medium

  * Initial public release under AGPL-3.0-or-later (see LICENSE for supplemental
    anti-AI-training terms)
  * CLI: --diagnose, --refetch, and manual --apply/--old-ip for scripting
  * Profiles: declarative multi-resource definitions under
    ~/.config/chaddr/profile/ (override with CHADDR_PROFILE_DIR)
  * Profile header fields: description, version, and addr-history (whitespace-
    separated historical IPv4/IPv6, equivalent to --old-ip for hosts/BIND
    matching)
  * Profile syntax: shell-style line continuation with trailing backslash
  * Resource types: AWS/Aliyun Elastic IP (diagnose, renew), Namecheap
    registered nameserver, hosts file, and BIND zone database (diagnose, apply)
  * from: resolve block for DNS-based current address discovery
  * GUI: wxWidgets profile editor with per-profile Logging and Diagnostics
    notebook tabs, status indicators (busy/error/ok), parallel diagnose,
    sequential renew, hosts apply preview, and Ctrl+E to open profiles in the
    system text editor
  * GUI: preserve log/diagnostic tab content for profiles not in the current
    run; only reset tabs for profiles being diagnosed or renewed/applied
  * GUI: isolate spare address sets per profile on multi-profile diagnose
  * Example profile shipped as profile/example
  * Man pages: chaddr(1) and chaddr-profile(5); version substituted at build
    time from git describe via Meson
  * Meson build/install with generated buildconfig install paths, launcher
    script, bash completion, and optional profile/doc install dirs
  * Debian packaging: /usr/bin/chaddr, man pages, bash completion, example
    profiles under /usr/share/chaddr/profile/

 -- Lenik (谢继雷) <lenik@bodz.net>  Wed, 24 Jun 2026 19:49:42 +0800
